\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  As a chronicler of the times and the auguries of the Vizjerei, Dumal Lunnash had largely been overlooked, but his texts had led Cholik through a macabre and twisted trail that had ended in the desolation of the forgotten city on the Dyre River.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93No,\'94 Raithen said. \'93Legends like that are everywhere. I\'92ve even followed a few of them myself, but I\'92ve never seen one come true.\'94
