\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Cholik knew what real power was. It was the reason he\'92d come there to Tauruk\'92s Port to find long-buried Ransim, which had died during the Sin War that had lasted centuries as Chaos had quietly but violently warred with the Light. That war had been long ago and played out in the east, before Westmarch had become civilized or powerful. Many cities and towns had been buried during those times. Most of them, though, had been shorn of their valuables. But Ransim had been hidden from the bulk of the Sin War. Even though the general populace knew nothing of the Sin War except that battles were fought\'97though not because the demons and the Light warred\'97they\'92d known nothing of Ransim. The port city had been an enigma, something that shouldn\'92t have existed. But some of the eastern mages had chosen that place to work and hide in, and they\'92d left secrets behind. Dumal Lunnash\'92s texts had been the only source Cholik had found regarding Ransim\'92s whereabouts, and even that book had led only to an arduous task of gathering information about the location that was hidden in carefully constructed lies and half-truths.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
