\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93If I live,\'94 the woman said, \'93you\'92ll need to look over your shoulder every day for the rest of your life. Because if I ever find you, I\plain \f2\i\fs24 will\plain \f2\fs24 kill you.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Still grinning, feeling better about life in general and surprised at how it had all come about, Raithen nodded. \'93I know you will, woman. And if I was an overconfident{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint39}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint39}braggart like a certain old priest, let\'92s say, I\'92d probably make the mistake of humbling you, then leaving you alive. Most people you could probably terrify and never have to worry about.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The woman pushed herself to her feet in open rebellion.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93But you and me, woman,\'94 Raithen went on, \'93we\'92re different. People judge us like we were nothing, that everything we say is just pomp and doggerel. They don\'92t understand that once we start hating them and plotting for them to fall, we\'92re only waiting for them to show a weakness we can exploit.\'94 He paused. \'93Just like you\'92ll suffer through every indignity I pass on your way to break you, and then remain strong enough to try to kill me.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  She stood and faced him, blood smearing her chin.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Raithen smiled at her again, and this time the effort was warm and genuine. \'93I want to thank you for that, for squaring my beam and trimming my sails. Reminds me of the true course I have to follow in this endeavor. No matter how many scraps Loremaster Buyard Cholik tosses my way, I\'92m no hound to be chasing bones and suffering ill use at his hands.\'94 He crossed to her.
