\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The enjoyment,\'94 Raithen said with a forced calm because he still wanted to know how bad the wound on his neck was, \'93was not all mine.\'94 He released the dead woman, and she thumped to the floor at his feet.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  As captain of some of the most vicious pirates to sail the Great Sea and the Gulf of Westmarch, he had an image to maintain. If any of his crew sensed weakness, someone would try to exploit it. He\'92d taken his own captaincy of\plain \f2\i\fs24 Barracuda\plain \f2\fs24 at the same time he\'92d taken his former captain\'92s life.
