\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Cholik strode toward the door, drawing on the remaining dregs of his strength. His legs felt like lead, and his heart hammered against his ribs. He\'92d pushed himself too far. He knew that. The confrontation with Raithen and the spell he\'92d summoned to destroy the rats had shoved him past his limits. His breath felt tight in his chest. Using magic no longer came easy to the aged and infirm sometimes. Spellwork had its own demands and often left those too weak to handle the energies warped and broken. And he\'92d come into the spells late in life after wasting so many years in the Zakarum Church.
