\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Bull walked into the small cargo hold. Raithen followed, inhaling the familiar stink. When he\'92d been with the Westmarch Navy, ships were not allowed to stink so. Sailors had been kept busy cleaning them out, dosing them with salt water and vinegar to kill any fungus or mold that tried to leach into the wood.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The boy was kept in the small brig in the stern of the cog.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint75}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint75}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  After unlocking the brig door, Bull shoved his big head in, then pulled it out just as quickly. He reached up and caught a board aimed at his face, then tugged on it.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The boy flopped onto the ship\'92s deck, landing hard on his belly and face. Quick as a fish taken out of water, the boy tried to get to his feet. Bull pinned him to the ship\'92s deck with one massive boot.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Incredibly, the boy revealed a huge knowledge of vituperative name-calling.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Like I said, cap\'92n,\'94 Bull said with a grin, \'93this \'92un here, why, he\'92d make for a fine pirate, he would.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Captain?\'94 the boy squalled. Even trapped under Bull\'92s foot, he craned his head around and tried to gaze up. \'93You\'92re the captain of this pigsty? Why, if I was you, I\'92d sew a bag for my head and only leave myself one eyehole out of embarrassment.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  In the first real amusement he\'92d felt that night, Raithen glanced down at the boy. \'93He\'92s not afraid, Bull?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Afraid?\'94 the boy squealed. \'93I\'92m afraid I\'92m going to die of boredom. You\'92ve had me for five days now. Three of them spent here in this ship. When I get back to my da and he speaks with his brother, the king, why, I\'92ll come back here and help wallop you myself.\'94 He clenched his fists and beat the deck. \'93Let me up, and give me a sword. I\'92ll fight you. By the Light, I\'92ll give you the fight of your life.\'94
