\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Truly taken aback by the boy\'92s demeanor, Raithen studied him. The boy was lean and muscular, starting to lose his baby fat. Raithen guessed he was eleven or twelve, possibly even as much as thirteen. A thick shock of dark hair crowned the boy\'92s head, and the lantern light revealed that he had gray or green eyes.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Do you even know where you\'92re at, boy?\'94 Raithen asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93When the king\'92s navy pays you off or tracks you down,\'94 the boy said, \'93I\'92ll know where you are. Don\'92t you think that I won\'92t.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Squatting down, holding the lantern close to the boy\'92s face, Raithen shook the dagger sheathed along his arm free{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint76}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint76}again. He rammed the point into the wooden deck only an inch from the boy\'92s nose.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The last person to threaten me tonight,\'94 Raithen said in a hoarse voice, \'93died only minutes ago. I won\'92t mind killing another.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The boy\'92s eyes focused on the knife. He swallowed hard but remained silent.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I\'92ll have your name, boy,\'94 Raithen said.
