\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The yelling always made Meridor uncomfortable. The people always sounded so angry and so frightened. Da had always told her that the people weren\'92t that way; it was just that they were all so hopeful. Meridor couldn\'92t understand why anyone would want to walk down into the stone snake\'92s belly. But that was where the Way of Dreams was, and the Way of Dreams\'97according to Da\'97could accomplish all kinds of miracles. She had seen a few of them over the past year, but they hadn\'92t mattered much. No one she knew had ever been chosen by Dien-Ap-Sten.
