\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick gazed at the sword. The stink of the barn behind his father\'92s butcher shop returned to him.\plain \f2\i\fs24 You\'92ll never amount to anything!\plain \f2\fs24 his father had shouted.\plain \f2\i\fs24 You\'92re dumb, and you\'92re stupid, and you\'92re going to die dumb and stupid!\plain \f2\fs24 Days and weeks and years of that rolled through Darrick\'92s head. Pain tingled through his body again, reminding him of the whippings he\'92d endured and somehow survived. His father\'92s voice had often haunted him during the past year, and he\'92d tried to drown it in wine and spirits, in hard work and bleak disappointment.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  And in the guilt over Mat Hu-Ring\'92s death.
