\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Look out!\'94 Palat yelled.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  For one frozen moment, Darrick saw the thick pilings{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint299}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint299}supporting the parapet before him.\plain \f2\i\fs24 We\'92re too high\plain \f2\fs24 , he thought, realizing the cargo ship came up higher on the structure than they\'92d guessed.\plain \f2\i\fs24 The impact is going to turn us away.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  But he had forgotten about the sheer, unstoppable tonnage the wild winds drove before them. As cargo ships went, not many were loaded more compactly or more heavily than oil freighters.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Blue Zephyr\plain \f2\fs24 was loaded to the top with driving weight and powered by a whirling storm.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The ship slammed into the pilings, driving from their moorings against the riverbed, collapsing the parapet in a sudden stream of rubble, driving a wall of water up and into the swirling winds so that a sudden monsoon rained down.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Blue Zephyr\'92\plain \f2\fs24 s starboard side took a beating as rock fell from above. Shudders ran the length of the ship, feeling like monstrous blows from a blacksmith\'92s hammer.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Blue Zephyr\plain \f2\fs24 was the anvil, and just as unrelenting and uncompromising. Rock and rubble bounced from the deck, which was canted hard to starboard as it scraped along the exposed riverbank.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The church\'92s guards fell amid the rubble as well. Darrick watched them fall, some of them dropping into the foaming river current on the starboard side of the ship and others bouncing across the deck, caught up in an avalanche of stone and mortar. Two of the guards fell into the flaming canvas on the forward mast. They screamed and dove from the rigging, candle flames burning brightly till they plunged into the river.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Releasing the wheel, knowing he could no longer attempt to hold it in place without risking dire injury, Darrick stepped back and seized the railing. He held on as the ship battled the wind and the riverbank. Pulling himself along the railing, he reached up for a ratline running to stern, caught it, and forced his way to the port side.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Blue Zephyr\plain \f2\fs24 ground to a halt on rock.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick heard the rock scraping along the ship\'92s hull, giant\'92s teeth worrying at a bone. He winced as he realized the amount of damage they\'92d done to the vessel and the{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint300}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint300}countless hours of work it would take to get her seaworthy again. He gazed over the deck, wondering if, after all they\'92d risked, they\'92d accomplished what they set out to do.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Shadows clung to the fallen debris and the dark mud of the riverbank. Darrick searched the riverbed but didn\'92t see the threatened sewer system Taramis\'92s research had turned up. Still, despite the grimness of their situation, no real fear touched Darrick. All he felt was an anxiety and a hope that the desperate madness of guilt of the last year would soon be over. Kabraxis\'92s church guards wouldn\'92t let them live after the assault.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis joined Darrick at the railing. The sage spoke a word and pointed to the torch he held. Flames instantly wreathed the torch, and light glared down over the ship\'92s side.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93That torch is going to light us up for the crossbowmen,\'94 Farranan said as he stood at the railing.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We can\'92t stay here,\'94 Rhambal said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Blue Zephyr\plain \f2\fs24 continued to rub and buck against the exposed limestone of the riverbed.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The ship\'92s not going to be here for long, either,\'94 Darrick said. For the first time he noticed the quiet that was left after the storm winds had died away. \'93The current\'92s going to dislodge us, sweep us away.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Thrusting the torch out, Taramis scanned the riverbank. More rock dropped from the broken parapet.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
