\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 In the distance, the splash of the closing guards running through the sewer grew steadily louder in Darrick\'92s ears. At least in this part of the tunnel, the water level was a few inches below knee-high, and the current was weak, little more than a steady flow.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 Darrick felt betrayed. The voice that he\'92d thought had been Mat\'92s had only been another demon-spawned trick. Staring at the sword, he knew it had been bait for an insidious trap.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  No,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 This is where ye\'92re supposed to be. Just hold yer water, I say, an\'92 things will be revealed to ye.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What things?\'94 Darrick demanded.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis and the other warriors turned to watch him, and the splashing of the approaching church guards grew louder, more immediate.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  There were three of us in that cavern when Kabraxis stepped through into our world,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat answered\plain \f2\i\fs24 . The magicks that Buyard Cholik unleashed when he opened that gateway to the Burning Hells marked all of us. Them doubts in yer head, Darrick, that\'92s just Kabraxis playing on yer fears. Just hold the course.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Three?\'94 Darrick repeated. \'93There weren\'92t three of us.\'94 Unless Buyard Cholik was being counted.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  There was another,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat insisted.\plain \f2\i\fs24 We all lost somethin\'92 that night, Darrick, an\'92 now we must stand together to get it back. Demons never enter this world without sowing the seeds of their own destruction. It\'92s up to men to figure out what they are. Me? I been lost for a long time, an\'92 it wasn\'92t until ye found Hauklin\'92s sword that I come back to meself and ye.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint327}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint327}\plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick shook his head, doubting all of it.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  You\'92re worthless, boy,\plain \f2\fs24 his father\'92s voice said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Hardly worth the time to kill you. Maybe I\'92ll just wait until you get a little bigger, put a little more meat on your bones, then I\'92ll dress you out and tell everybody you up and ran away.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The old fear vibrated through Darrick. In the shadows he thought he could almost see his father\'92s face.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Darrick,\'94 Taramis called.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Even though he heard the man clearly, Darrick found he couldn\'92t respond. He was trapped by the memory and by the old fear. The stink of the stables behind the butcher\'92s shop filled his nostrils, making the images of the men before him and the sewer tunnel around him seem dreamlike.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  C\'92mon, Darrick!\plain \f2\fs24 Mat called.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Pay attention, damn ye! This is the hold that Kabraxis has found over ye. Me, why, that foul demon up an\'92 lost me out in the ghost ways, an\'92 maybe I\'92d be there still if ye hadn\'92t found Hauklin\'92s blade the way ye done.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick felt the sword in his fist, but he blamed it for leading them into the dead end. Maybe Mat still believed the sword was a talisman of power, something to stand tall against the demons, but Darrick didn\'92t. It was a cursed thing, like other weapons he\'92d talked about. Palat had owned a cursed weapon; he knew what he was talking about when he denounced Hauklin\'92s sword.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  It\'92s the demon, Darrick,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Be strong.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I can\'92t,\'94 Darrick whispered hollowly. He watched the torchlights of the approaching guards gather at the far end of the tunnel.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93You can\'92t what?\'94 Taramis asked him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I can\'92t believe,\'94 Darrick said. All his life he\'92d trained himself not to believe. He didn\'92t believe that his father had hated him. He didn\'92t believe that it was his father\'92s fault that he was beaten. He\'92d trained himself to believe that life was one day after another at the butcher\'92s shop and that a good day was one when a beating didn\'92t cripple him up.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  But ye escaped that,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I ran,\'94 Darrick whispered, \'93but I couldn\'92t outrun what was meant to be.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint328}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint328}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Ye have.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93No,\'94 Darrick said, gazing at the guard.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93They\'92re waiting,\'94 Palat said. \'93They figure there\'92s too many of us for them to take without losing more than a few of their own. They\'92re going to hold up, get more archers in here, then take us down.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis stepped toward Darrick. \'93Are you all right?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick didn\'92t answer. Helplessness filled him, and he struggled to push it away. The feeling settled over his chest and shoulders, making it hard for him to breathe. For this past year, he\'92d put his life into a bottle, into the bottom of a glass, into the cheap wine in every lowdown tavern he\'92d wandered through. Then he\'92d made the mistake of trying to sober himself up and believe there was more than futility in his life.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  More than the bad luck and the feeling of being unwanted that had haunted him all his life.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Worthless,\plain \f2\fs24 his father\'92s voice spat.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  And why had he saved himself? To die at the end of a collapsed sewer like a rat? Darrick wanted to laugh, but he wanted to cry as well.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Darrick,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat called.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93No, Mat,\'94 Darrick said. \'93I\'92ve come far enough. It\'92s time to end it.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Moving closer, holding the lantern he held up to Darrick\'92s face, Taramis stared into his eyes. \'93Darrick.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We\'92ve come here to die,\'94 Darrick said, telling Mat as well as Taramis.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We didn\'92t come here to die,\'94 Taramis said. \'93We\'92ve come here to expose the demon for what he is. Once the people here who worship him know what he is, they will turn from him and be free.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The malaise that possessed Darrick was so strong that the sage\'92s words barely registered on him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  It\'92s the demon,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Are you talking to your friend?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Mat\'92s dead,\'94 Darrick said in a hoarse whisper. \'93I saw him die. I got him killed.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Is he here with us?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint329}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint329}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick shook his head, but the movement felt distant from him, as if it were someone else\'92s body. \'93No. He\'92s dead.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93But he\'92s talking to you,\'94 the sage said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It\'92s a lie,\'94 Darrick answered.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  It\'92s not a lie, ye bloody great fool!\plain \f2\fs24 Mat exploded.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Damn ye, ye thick-headed mullet. Ye was always the hardest to convince of somethin\'92 ye couldn\'92t see, couldn\'92t touch for yerself. But if ye don\'92t listen to me now, Darrick Lang, I\'92m gonna be travelin\'92 the ghost ways forever. I\'92ll never know no rest, never be at peace. Would ye wish that on me?
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93No,\'94 Darrick said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What is he saying?\'94 Taramis asked. \'93Have we come to the right place?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It\'92s a trick,\'94 Darrick said. \'93Mat says that the demon is in my head, trying to weaken me. And he\'92s telling me he\'92s not the demon.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Do you believe him?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I believe the demon is in my head,\'94 Darrick said. \'93I\'92ve somehow betrayed you all, Taramis. I apologize.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93No,\'94 Taramis said. \'93The sword is true. It came to you.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It was a demon\'92s trick.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The sage shook his head. \'93No demon, not even Kabraxis, could have power over Hauklin\'92s sword.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  But Darrick remembered how the sword had resisted him, how it hadn\'92t come free at first down in that hidden tomb.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  The sword couldn\'92t be freed at first,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 It couldn\'92t. It had to wait on me. It took us both, ye see. That\'92s why I was wanderin\'92 the ghost ways, stuck between hither an\'92 thither. That\'92s me part of this. An\'92 the third man, why, he\'92s yer way out, he is.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The third man is the way out,\'94 Darrick repeated dully.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis studied him, moving the lantern in front of Darrick\'92s eyes.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Despite the irritation he felt at having the light so close to his eyes, Darrick found that he couldn\'92t move.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  You ain\'92t my son,\plain \f2\fs24 his father roared in his mind.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Folks look at you, and they wouldn\'92t blame me if I killed your mother. But she\'92s bewitched me. I can\'92t even raise a hand to her.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Pain exploded along Darrick\'92s cheek, but it was pain{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint330}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint330}from the memory, not something that was happening at present. The boy he\'92d been had landed in a heap on a pile of dung-covered straw. And his father had closed in and beaten him, causing Darrick to spend days lying in the stable with fever and a broken arm.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Why didn\'92t I die then?\'94 Darrick asked. Everything would have been so much easier, so much simpler.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Mat would still have been alive, still living in Hillsfar with his family.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  I chose not to be there,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 I chose to go with me friend. An\'92 if ye hadn\'92t given me reason to get out of Hillsfar, I\'92d have gotten out of there on me own. Hillsfar wasn\'92t that big a place for the likes of ye and me. Me da knew that, just like he knew about me leavin\'92 for ye.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I killed you,\'94 Darrick said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  An\'92 if it wasn\'92t for ye, how many times over dead would I have been by now? Before we ended up at Tauruk\'92s Port?
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  In his mind, Darrick saw Mat slam into the cliff wall again, the skeleton hanging to him like a leech.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  How many times did them captains we crewed with tell us that the life of a Westmarch Navy sailor wasn\'92t worth havin\'92? Long hours, short pay, an\'92 an even shorter life was it come to that, as it most likely would. The only things what made it all worthwhile was yer shipmates an\'92 what few tavern wenches would roll their eyes at ye like ye was some kind of big damn hero.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick remembered those speeches and those times. Mat had always made the best of it, always got the prettiest wenches, always had the most friends.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  An\'92 I\'92d be knowin\'92 if me luck holds true in the hereafter,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said,\plain \f2\i\fs24 were I ever to get finished with this last bit of business we signed on for. Take up the sword, Darrick, an\'92 stand ready. The third man is comin\'92.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Part of the malaise lifted from Darrick. Only then did he realize that Taramis had gripped the front of his shirt in both fists and was shaking him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Darrick,\'94 the sage said. \'93Darrick.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I hear you.\'94 Darrick heard the thunk of quarrels meeting the metal shields that the other warriors held up as{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint331}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint331}well. Evidently the church guards had grown braver and decided to pick some of them off if they could. At the moment, the warriors were able to keep the shields overlapping so that none of the fletched missiles got through.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What third man?\'94 Taramis demanded.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I don\'92t know.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Is there a way out of this?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I don\'92t know.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Desperation creased the sage\'92s face. \'93Use the sword.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93I don\'92t know how.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Ye\'92re waitin\'92\plain \f2\fs24 , Mat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We\'92re waiting,\'94 Darrick repeated dully. He\'92d dwindled so close inside himself that nothing mattered. His father\'92s voice was muted, somewhere in the background. Maybe Mat had found a way to keep it quiet, but if he believed that, then Mat couldn\'92t be the demon, and Darrick was pretty certain that the demon inside his head was Mat, too.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93There\'92s other guards coming,\'94 Palat announced.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Without warning, stone shifted against stone.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis glanced over Darrick\'92s shoulder. \'93Look,\'94 the sage said. \'93Perhaps your friend was right.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Numbly, Darrick turned and spotted the rectangular hole that opened in the sewer ceiling above the pile of rubble. Peering closer, he realized it wasn\'92t a door that had opened but rather a large section of rock that had been lifted up and out of the way. Light shone on the rubble and the water below.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  A man shoved his head through the rectangle. \'93Darrick Lang,\'94 he called.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Shifting his lantern, Taramis brought the man into view.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Staring into the burned wreckage of the man\'92s face, Darrick didn\'92t believe for a moment that help had arrived.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Darrick Lang,\'94 the burned man called again.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He knows you,\'94 Taramis said at Darrick\'92s side. \'93Who is he?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Shaking his head, unable to recognize the burned man\'92s features in the shifting of light and shadows, Darrick said, \'93I don\'92t know.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint332}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint332}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Ye know him,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 That\'92s Cap\'92n Raithen. From the pirates what was at Tauruk\'92s Port. Ye fought him aboard the pirate ship.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Amazed, knowing somehow Mat was speaking the truth, Darrick recognized the man. \'93But he died.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He looks like he did,\'94 Taramis agreed in a quiet voice, \'93but he\'92s offering us a way out of certain death. He\'92s certainly mastered close escapes.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93This way,\'94 Raithen said. \'93If you would live, hurry. That damned demon has sent more people into the tunnel after you, and now that they\'92ve seen me open this one, they\'92re likely to check up with the maps and figure out how I got here.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Come on,\'94 Taramis said, taking Darrick by the arm.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It\'92s a trick,\'94 Darrick argued.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  No,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 We\'92re joined, the three of us. Joined in this endeavor.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We stay here, and we\'92ll die like fish in a barrel,\'94 Taramis said. He shoved Darrick into reluctant movement.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  As they neared the debris pile, the rats scattered, and quarrels struck the stones and sometimes the rats, but luckily the warriors all got through.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Raithen shoved his hand down toward Darrick. \'93Give me the sword,\'94 the pirate captain said. \'93I\'92ll help you up.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Before Darrick could move the sword, Raithen reached down for it. As soon as the man\'92s fingers touched the sword, they hissed.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Raithen yelped and yanked his hand back. Fresh steam rose from his burned fingers as he retreated into the tunnel above the sewer. He cursed and broke two more rocks free, enlarging the space so the demon hunters could more easily gain entrance.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis went through first, clambering into the smaller tunnel above them. Dully, Darrick followed, taking care to watch the enchanted sword.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  After introducing himself, Taramis offered his hand. The pirate captain remained out of arm\'92s reach and ignored the hand. His gaze focused on Darrick. \'93Has your dead friend been in touch with you?\'94 the pirate captain demanded.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint333}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint333}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick looked at him, unwilling to answer. If anything, Darrick was ready to put Hauklin\'92s sword through the pirate captain\'92s heart.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  A cold smile framed Raithen\'92s lips. Cracks opened in the burned flesh, and blood beaded his mouth. \'93You don\'92t have to answer,\'94 the pirate captain said. \'93There was no other way you\'92d be here if it weren\'92t for your meddling friend.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Meddlin\'92 friend, is it, then?\plain \f2\fs24 Mat demanded.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Why, if I could put me hands on ye, or take a good length of steel up to do battle, I\'92d have the head off yer shoulders for that, ye mangy swab.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He\'92s still with us, I see,\'94 Raithen said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Surprised, Darrick asked, \'93You can hear him?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Whenever he\'92s around, aye. He prattles on constantly. I just thank the Light that I\'92ve only listened to him these past few weeks.\'94 Raithen\'92s gaze dropped to the sword in Darrick\'92s hand. \'93He told me you\'92d come bearing Hauklin\'92s mighty blade. Is that it?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Aye,\'94 Darrick replied.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The other warriors clambered into the small tunnel and milled around. Taramis issued quiet orders, getting men on either side of the opening in the bottom of the new tunnel.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93And that will kill Kabraxis?\'94 Raithen demanded.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93So I\'92ve been told,\'94 Darrick replied. \'93Or at least drive the demon from this world back to the Burning Hells.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Spitting blood onto the tunnel floor, Raithen said, \'93I\'92d rather we gutted him and threw him to the sharks, then watched them carry him away a bite at a time.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The church guards are coming,\'94 Palat said. \'93We\'92d best be on our way.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Running through this tunnel with them on our heels?\'94 Raithen asked. He grimaced, and the bloody froth at his mouth made him look demented.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  He is demented,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 What Kabraxis did to him has nearly taken his sanity.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What are you doing here?\'94 Darrick demanded of Raithen.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The pirate captain smiled, and more blood flecked his{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint334}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint334}lips. \'93The same as you, I expect. I came to be free of the demon. Although, after hearing of your friend\'92s death and knowing what\'92s happened to me, I\'92d have to say that you appear to have gotten better treatment than any of us.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick didn\'92t say anything.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Splashing sounded in the sewer below.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Those church guards aren\'92t going to wait for you two to finish palavering,\'94 Palat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Raithen stepped back and pulled a barrel from the wall beside the opening. As he yanked on the heavy barrel, the skin covering his hands split and bled. Crimson stained the barrel as Darrick and Palat lent hands, pushing the barrel toward the opening in the floor. Yanking the lid from the barrel, the pirate captain revealed the dark oil inside.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Pour,\'94 Raithen commanded.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Together, they poured the contents of the barrel into the sewer water and over the rocks below. Rats scampered from beneath the dark liquid, and the guards held their positions warily.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Two crossbow quarrels flew through the opening in the floor. One of them splintered through the side of the barrel, and the other sliced through Raithen\'92s right calf. Cursing with the pain, Raithen reached back to the wall and yanked a torch from the sconce there. He tossed the torch through the hole in the floor and onto the pile of debris below.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Peering cautiously over the side of the hole, Darrick watched as the oil caught fire. Flames spread over the pile of rubble, chasing the rats from their hiding places and onto the guards and into the water. The oil floating on top of the water caught fire as well. Carried by the slow current of the sewer, flames floated toward the guards, forcing them to retreat.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93That will buy us some time,\'94 Raithen said. He turned to the left and hurried along the tunnel.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Where are you taking us?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93To the demon,\'94 Raithen said. \'93That\'92s where we\'92ve got to go.\'94 He ran down the tunnel, pausing only long enough to take another torch from a sconce farther on.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint335}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint335}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The passageway was smaller than the sewer below, only wide enough for three warriors to jog abreast. Drawn by the urgency that vibrated within him, Darrick took the lead position among the demon hunters, joined quickly by Taramis and Palat.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Who is that man?\'94 Taramis asked, eyes locked on the fleeing figure ahead of them.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Raithen,\'94 Darrick replied. \'93He is\'97\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Was,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat assured him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93\'97\plain \f2\i\fs24 was\plain \f2\fs24 ,\'94 Darrick amended, \'93a pirate captain in the Gulf of Westmarch. A year ago, Raithen worked with Buyard Cholik.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The Zakarum priest who opened the gateway for Kabraxis?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Aye.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What happened to him?\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He was killed by the demon in Tauruk\'92s Port,\'94 Darrick said, knowing how strange it sounded as they watched the burned madman racing before them.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He\'92s not dead enough to my way of thinking,\'94 Palat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  At the same time Raithen was killed,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said,\plain \f2\i\fs24 Kabraxis also cast the spell to raise the zombies an\'92 skeletons to pursue us. The magic pervaded Raithen\'92s corpse afterward, causin\'92 him to rise again. After ye freed the sword, I was drawn here to him. I found I could talk to him as I talk to ye. The three of us are bound, Darrick, an\'92 in our bindin\'92, we present the way to end Kabraxis\'92s reign here.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93He\'92s dead,\'94 Darrick explained, giving the details that Mat had given him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The prophecy of Hauklin,\'94 Taramis said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What prophecy?\'94 Darrick asked. They trailed after Raithen, following the pirate captain around a bend in the tunnel.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It was said that Hauklin\'92s sword would never be taken from his tomb except to unite the Three,\'94 the sage said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What three?\'94 Darrick asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint336}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint336}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  TWENTY-FIVE
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\pict\jpegblip\picw29\pich23 }
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \'93One lost in death, one lost in life, and one lost in himself,\'94 Taramis said. \'93One trapped in the past, one trapped in the present, and one trapped in the future.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 A cold chill of dread filled Darrick.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Your friend Mat must be the one who is trapped in death, unreleased by his death in the past. Raithen has to be the one trapped in life, unable to die and doomed to live out the way he is through the present.\'94 He gazed at Darrick. \'93That leaves you.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Why didn\'92t you mention this earlier?\'94 Darrick asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Because not all prophecies are true,\'94 the sage answered. \'93All weapons and artifacts have stories that are told about them, but not all of those stories are true. When you drew the sword from Hauklin\'92s body, I thought the prophecy was false.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taramis\'92s words hammered Darrick.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Aye,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said inside his head,\plain \f2\i\fs24 ye\'92ve been the one lost in yerself. But them sad times is behind ye. Just like Hillsfar an\'92 that stable behind yer father\'92s butcher shop. Just ye keep that in yer head, an\'92 ye\'92re gonna be all right. I\'92ll not desert ye.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The prophecy goes on,\'94 Taramis said. \'93One will lift the sword, one will provide the way, and one will face the demon.\'94 The sage stared at Darrick. \'93You couldn\'92t lift the sword at first because your friend wasn\'92t with you then. You couldn\'92t lift the sword till you heard Mat\'92s voice.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick knew it was true, and in a way it made sense with all the events that had transpired since.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93And he shows us the way,\'94 Taramis said, pointing at{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint337}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint337}Raithen still running before them. \'93That leaves you to face the demon.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Beside the sage,\'94 Palat snorted derisively.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick\'92s face flamed in embarrassment, knowing the warrior didn\'92t believe him strong enough or brave enough to confront the demon even with Hauklin\'92s enchanted sword. And truth to tell, he didn\'92t feel strong enough or brave enough himself.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Worthless,\plain \f2\fs24 his father\'92s voice said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Cringing inside, Darrick desperately wanted out of the course of action left before him. He was no hero. At best, he would have made a decent Westmarch naval officer; perhaps\'97but only perhaps\'97he might have made a decent ship\'92s captain.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  But a hero?
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  No. Darrick couldn\'92t accept that. But if he left, if he walked away from this confrontation to save himself, what would be left of him? Cold realization flooded him, and his footing nearly faltered. If he backed away from the coming battle, he knew he would be everything his father had ever accused him of being.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  And if he did that, he would be as trapped between life and death as Mat or Raithen.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  There\'92s salvation in this for us all,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Even if I become a martyr?\plain \f2\fs24 Darrick wondered.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93We got men behind us,\'94 Clavyn called from the rear of the warriors.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93It\'92s the guards,\'94 Raithen said. \'93I told you they\'92d find us. This tunnel is one of the newer ones. They use it to bring supplies into the church. Secret passageways and tunnels honeycomb these buildings. Over the last few weeks, I\'92ve ferreted out most of them.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Where are you taking us?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93To the central cathedral,\'94 Raithen answered. \'93If you want to face Kabraxis, you\'92ll find him and Cholik there.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Only a few feet farther on, the pirate captain came to a halt under a slanted section of ceiling. The door was as slanted as the ceiling, fitting into it.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 {\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint338}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint338}
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93Guards sometimes wait here,\'94 Raithen said. \'93But they\'92re not here now. They went below to help trap you in the sewer, not knowing the way the tunnel overlapped the sewer as I did.\'94 He pulled himself up and peered through a slit.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick joined the man, keeping his sword naked in his fist. Taramis stood on the other side of him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Gazing out through the slit, Darrick saw Buyard Cholik standing on a platform on top of a huge stone snake with a flaming face. As Darrick watched, the snake bobbed and weaved above the expectant audience. The way the audience beseeched and cried out to the snake and the man atop it left a sick knot in Darrick\'92s stomach. He knew a few of the worshippers might know they prostrated themselves before evil, but most of them didn\'92t. They were innocents, praying for miracles and never knowing they were being preyed on by a hell-spawned demon.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93There are hundreds, maybe thousands of people out there,\'94 Palat said in wonderment as he crowded up to the viewing slit as well. \'93If we step out into that, we\'92re going to be outnumbered.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93The crowd will also give us a means of escaping,\'94 Taramis said. \'93The church guards won\'92t be able to seal off all the exits and keep the crowd under control. Once we kill Buyard Cholik, there should be confusion enough to cover our retreat. After that, we\'92ll spread the truth about Kabraxis through the city.\'94
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93You can\'92t kill Buyard Cholik,\'94 Raithen said.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick looked at the pirate captain. Aware of the pounding boots echoing down the tunnel, Darrick knew they didn\'92t have much time.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  \'93What do you mean?\'94 Taramis asked.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
