\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  The pirate captain reached beneath his robe and brought out a handheld crossbow. Along his burn-blackened hands, thick, crusty scabs cracked open and leaked blood. A madman\'92s grin fitted itself to his bloody lips as he reached for a small lever overhead. He gazed at Darrick. \'93Don\'92t fail me, sailor. I crossed blades with you before, aboard\plain \f2\i\fs24 Barracuda.\plain \f2\fs24 Be as good now as you were then. And be everything your little dead friend said you could be.\'94
