\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Taking advantage of Cholik\'92s inability to fight against him, Darrick caught the edge of the platform in his other hand, then pulled himself up. Cholik stepped backward, freed from Darrick\'92s grip, and fell over the platform\'92s edge.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  The sword!\plain \f2\fs24 Mat yelled in Darrick\'92s head.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Kabraxis is still ahead of ye!
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Clinging to the platform mounted behind the snake\'92s bobbing head, watching the movement around him with his peripheral vision, Darrick held fast to the platform with his left hand and stretched his right out for the sword. He willed it to come back to him just as he had that day at Ellig Barrows\'92s house.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Even as Cholik\'92s corpse fell toward the cracked stone floor below, Darrick felt the power binding him to the sword. He watched as the enchanted blade pulled free of the dead man. Hauklin\'92s sword was in the air, streaking toward Darrick as the snake suddenly popped its head up, flinging him high into the air and knocking the sword away.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Whirling, almost colliding with the cathedral ceiling because he was thrown so high, Darrick flailed and tried to get control of his body. Horrified, he watched as the snake lowered its head below him and opened its massive jaws.{\*\bkmkstart RichViewCheckpoint345}{\*\bkmkend RichViewCheckpoint345}Flames roiled in the snake\'92s throat, promising a fiery death if it caught him.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Get the sword!\plain \f2\fs24 Mat yelled.\plain \f2\i\fs24 If ye don\'92t have the sword, ye ain\'92t got nothin\'92!
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick focused on the sword, but he couldn\'92t clear his mind of the snake below as he reached the apex of his flight and started back down. Even if the snake somehow missed him, he felt certain that he wouldn\'92t survive the fall.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  The sword!\plain \f2\fs24 Mat cried.\plain \f2\i\fs24 The sword will protect ye if ye have it. An\'92 I can help ye through the sword\'92s magic.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\fs24 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  Darrick pushed thoughts of death from him. If he died, it would only put an end to the pain he\'92d lived in for the last year, and from all the pain he\'92d borne in those years before that.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0  He concentrated on Hauklin\'92s sword, strengthening the bond he felt between the weapon and himself. Cholik\'92s corpse plummeted toward the waiting stone floor beside the yawning snake\'92s mouth. But the enchanted blade pulled free of the dead man and flew toward Darrick\'92s waiting hand.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f2\i\fs24  Hold to the sword,\plain \f2\fs24 Mat said.\plain \f2\i\fs24 Hold to the sword that I may help ye.
